TITLE: Defining Assignment Rules for Nx Agents in YAML
DESCRIPTION: Example YAML configuration for assignment rules using Nx Agents. It defines distribution settings and rules for specific projects, targets, and configurations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nrwl/nx/blob/master/docs/nx-cloud/reference/assignment-rules.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: yaml
CODE:
```
distribute-on:
  default: 5 linux-medium-js, 5 linux-large-js

assignment-rules:
  - projects:
      - app1
    targets:
      - e2e-ci*
    configurations:
      - production
    run-on:
      - agent: linux-medium
        parallelism: 5

  - targets:
      - lint
      - build
    run-on:
      - agent: linux-large
        parallelism: 10
```

