TITLE: Implementing targetDefaults in nx.json
DESCRIPTION: A centralized configuration in nx.json that defines default settings for build, lint, and test targets using the targetDefaults property, reducing repetition across projects.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nrwl/nx/blob/master/docs/shared/recipes/running-tasks/reduce-repetitive-configuration.md#2025-04-22_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "targetDefaults": {
    "build": {
      "executor": "@nx/js:tsc",
      "outputs": ["{options.outputPath}"],
      "options": {
        "outputPath": "dist/{projectRoot}",
        "main": "{projectRoot}/src/index.ts",
        "tsConfig": "{projectRoot}/tsconfig.lib.json",
        "assets": ["{projectRoot}/*.md"]
      }
    },
    "lint": {
      "executor": "@nx/eslint:lint",
      "outputs": ["{options.outputFile}"],
      "options": {
        "lintFilePatterns": ["{projectRoot}/**/*.ts"]
      }
    },
    "test": {
      "executor": "@nx/jest:jest",
      "outputs": ["{workspaceRoot}/coverage/{projectRoot}"],
