TITLE: Configuring External Dependencies Constraints in Nx ESLint
DESCRIPTION: ESLint configuration for enforcing module boundaries and banning specific external package imports. It sets up rules for different project scopes (store, admin, core, shared) and prevents importing specific framework packages.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nrwl/nx/blob/master/docs/blog/2021-12-17-mastering-the-project-boundaries-in-nx.md#2025-04-22_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: json5
CODE:
```
{
  '@nrwl/nx/enforce-module-boundaries': [
    'error',
    {
      depConstraints: [
        {
          sourceTag: 'scope:store',
          onlyDependOnLibsWithTags: [
            'scope:store',
            'scope:shared',
            'scope:core',
          ],
          bannedExternalImports: ['@angular/*'],
        },
        {
          sourceTag: 'scope:admin',
          onlyDependOnLibsWithTags: [
            'scope:admin',
            'scope:shared',
            'scope:core',
          ],
          bannedExternalImports: ['react*'],
        },
        {
          sourceTag: 'scope:core',
          onlyDependOnLibsWithTags: ['scope:shared'],
          bannedExternalImports: ['@angular/*', 'react*'],
        },
        {
          sourceTag: 'scope:shared',
          onlyDependOnLibsWithTags: ['scope:shared'],
          bannedExternalImports: ['@angular/*', 'react*'],
        },
      ],
    },
  ]
}
```

