TITLE: Simple Signal-based Store Implementation
DESCRIPTION: Shows a basic store implementation using raw Signals with add, delete, and update operations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nrwl/nx/blob/master/docs/blog/2024-12-16-angular-state-management-2025.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
export class AppStore {
  readonly state = signal([]);

  add(item) {
    this.state.update((oldState) => [...oldState, item]);
  }
  delete(item) {
    this.state.update((oldState) => oldState.filter((e) => e.id !== item.id));
  }
  update(item) {
    this.state.update((oldState) =>
      oldState.map((e) => (e.id === item.id ? item : e))
    );
  }
}
```

