TITLE: Configuring ESLint Module Boundary Rules in Nx
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to configure ESLint with the `@nx/enforce-module-boundaries` rule to enforce module boundaries based on tags. It defines constraints specifying which tags a library can depend on based on its own tags. The configuration resides in the `eslint.config.mjs` file.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nrwl/nx/blob/master/nx-dev/tutorial/src/content/tutorial/3-angular-monorepo/2a-smart-monorepo/11-module-boundaries/content.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
export default [
  // ...
  {
    files: ['**/*.ts', '**/*.tsx', '**/*.js', '**/*.jsx'],
    rules: {
      '@nx/enforce-module-boundaries': [
        'error',
        {
          enforceBuildableLibDependency: true,
          allow: ['^.*/eslint(\.base)?\.config\.[cm]?js$'],
          depConstraints: [
            {
              sourceTag: 'type:feature',
              onlyDependOnLibsWithTags: ['type:feature', 'type:ui'],
            },
            {
              sourceTag: 'type:ui',
              onlyDependOnLibsWithTags: ['type:ui'],
            },
            {
              sourceTag: 'scope:orders',
              onlyDependOnLibsWithTags: [
                'scope:orders',
                'scope:products',
                'scope:shared',
              ],
            },
            {
              sourceTag: 'scope:products',
              onlyDependOnLibsWithTags: ['scope:products', 'scope:shared'],
            },
            {
              sourceTag: 'scope:shared',
              onlyDependOnLibsWithTags: ['scope:shared'],
            },
          ],
        },
      ],
    },
  },
  // ...
];
```

