TITLE: React Button Component Example
DESCRIPTION: This React component defines a simple button that increments a counter when clicked. The `useState` hook is used to manage the count. The `handleClick` function updates the count, and the button displays the number of times it has been clicked.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nrwl/nx/blob/master/docs/shared/recipes/storybook/interaction-tests.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import React, { useState } from 'react';

export function Button() {
  const [count, setCount] = useState(0);

  const handleClick = () => {
    setCount(count + 1);
  };

  return (
    <button role="button" onClick={handleClick}>
      You've clicked me {count} times
    </button>
  );
}

export default Button;
```

