TITLE: Configure Group-Specific Pre-Version Build Command in nx.json
DESCRIPTION: This configuration defines a `groupPreVersionCommand` within a release group in `nx.json`. This command runs the `build` target specifically for projects within the "my-group" release group before versioning.  It uses `nx run-many` to target the specified projects and ensures that they are built before the group's version is updated.  The global `preVersionCommand` will also execute.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nrwl/nx/blob/master/docs/shared/recipes/nx-release/build-before-versioning.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
  "release": {
    "groups": {
      "my-group": {
        "projects": ["my-lib-one", "my-lib-two"],
        "version": {
          "groupPreVersionCommand": "npx nx run-many -t build -p my-lib-one,my-lib-two"
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

