TITLE: Comprehensive package.json Configuration with Orchestration and Caching
DESCRIPTION: A more detailed package.json example showing how to configure Nx with advanced features including namedInputs, dependsOn, and outputs for optimizing task execution and caching.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nrwl/nx/blob/master/docs/shared/reference/project-configuration.md#2025-04-22_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: jsonc
CODE:
```
{
  "name": "mylib",
  "scripts": {
    "test": "jest",
    "build": "tsc -p tsconfig.lib.json", // the actual command here is arbitrary
    "ignored": "exit 1"
  },
  "nx": {
    "namedInputs": {
      "default": ["{projectRoot}/**/*"],
      "production": ["!{projectRoot}/**/*.spec.tsx"]
    },
    "targets": {
      "build": {
        "inputs": ["production", "^production"],
        "outputs": ["{workspaceRoot}/dist/libs/mylib"],
        "dependsOn": ["^build"]
      },
      "test": {
        "inputs": ["default", "^production"],
        "outputs": [],
        "dependsOn": ["build"]
      }
    },
    "includedScripts": ["test", "build"] // If you want to limit the scripts Nx sees, you can specify a list here.
  }
}
```

