TITLE: Importing Violating Module Boundary Rule in Nx
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet shows an example of importing a component from a library that violates the defined module boundary rules. The `Orders` component is imported from the `orders` library into the `products` library, which is not allowed based on the ESLint configuration.  This import will trigger an ESLint error.
SOURCE: https://github.com/nrwl/nx/blob/master/nx-dev/tutorial/src/content/tutorial/3-angular-monorepo/2a-smart-monorepo/11-module-boundaries/content.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import styles from './products.module.css';

// This import is not allowed 👇
import { Orders } from '@angular-monorepo/orders';

export function Products() {
  return (
    <div className={styles['container']}>
      <h1>Welcome to Products!</h1>
      <p>This is a change. 👋</p>
    </div>
  );
}

export default Products;
```

